other_tests.findings: Initial biopsy specimen demonstrated nonspecific lichenoid dermatitis. A repeat biopsy showed epidermal hyperplasia with a moderate degree of cellular atypia.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Nearly 3 years later, a biopsy specimen revealed loss of orderly epithelial architecture and full-thickness, severe cytologic atypia, characteristic of squamous cell carcinoma in situ.

other_tests.findings: Several biopsy specimens taken from involved skin sites revealed normal epidermis.
other_tests.changes_over_time: This occurred after treatment with 5% imiquimod cream, indicating a positive response to therapy.
